  "decision_conditions": [
    "1. The extraction flues hereby permitted shall be removed within 3 months of the date of this decision unless all external surfaces are painted a dark, matt colour.\r\n2. The extraction flues hereby permitted shall be removed within 6 weeks of the date of failure to meet any one of the requirements set out in (i) to (iv) below:-\r\n(i) within 3 months of the date of this decision full details of the following shall have been submitted for the written approval of the local planning authority: \r\n(a) the location of the filters within the ducting; \r\n(b) the identification of each filter by type, including a product specification from the manufacturer; \r\n(c) the efflux velocity for each duct; \r\n(d) where carbon filters are utilised, the dwell (residence) time of gases in the carbon filtration;\r\nand (e) a maintenance contract for the fume extraction and odour control system covering all filters and ducting. A timetable shall be produced for the implementation of any measure arising out of the submission of the details.\r\n(ii) within 11 months of the date of this decision the details referred to in condition (i) shall have been approved by the local planning authority or, if the local planning authority refuse to approve the details or fails to give a decision within the prescribed period, an appeal shall have been made to, and accepted as validly made by, the Secretary of State.\r\n(iii) If an appeal is made in pursuance of (ii) above, that appeal shall have been finally determined and the submitted scheme shall have been approved by the Secretary of State.\r\n(iv) The approved details shall have been carried out and completed in accordance with the approved timetable.\r\n3. The extraction equipment shall at all times be operated and maintained in accordance with the manufacturerâ€™s instructions."
